12. Report verbally to the Designated Safeguarding Lead (DSL) [1.13]. It is the responsibility of staff to report their concerns, not to investigate or decide whether a child has been abused [1.11.L21]. All school staff are required to pass on information which gives rise to a concern about a child's welfare [1.1].
13. Seek support if they feel distressed or need to debrief [1.13].

