*   "Keep arms and legs covered, even in warm weather" [1.11.L21]
*   "Display a change in behaviour - from quiet to aggressive, or happy-go-lucky to withdrawn" [1.11.L21]
*   "Frequently miss school or arrive late" [1.11.L21]

It is the responsibility of staff to report their concerns, not to investigate or decide whether a child has been abused [1.11.L21]. All concerns, however minor, should be reported, as staff do not need 'absolute proof' that the child is at risk [1.11.L21].

